msgid "What are your donations used for?"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Your donations guarantee our independence: they keep accounting for the "
"biggest share of our income until now."
msgstr ""

msgid "Expenses"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Our expected budget for 2026-2027 reaches 100 000 € and breaks down in 5 "
"categories."
msgstr ""

msgid "Project expenditure breaks down into the following categories:"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"**Development**: one-off funding awarded to some of the most work-intensive "
"features of [the roadmap](#roadmap) which require to ensure dedication over "
"the long-term of experienced contributors. It should be noted, however, that "
"this amount is negligible in relation to the voluntary work carried out by "
"the contributors overall - YunoHost remains primarily a volunteer-based "
"project."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"**Infrastructure**: corresponds to the hosting of the tools used by the "
"project, such as the website, documentation, forum, technical tools, etc. "
"The amount of this expenditure should reduce in 2025 following a migration "
"to a dedicated server from a friendly host provider."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"**Events**: expenses to enable the team to attend public events (e.g. JdLL) "
"and to meet in the same place at least twice a year to work together on "
"feature design and development strategy."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"**Facilitation**: financial compensation allocated to administrative tasks, "
"animation and coordination of the collective. This is a new type of expense "
"introduced in 2025, decided by the collective given the need to have a "
"person dedicated to these aspects (a.k.a “stirrer”)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"**Fees and other expenses**: bank charges or donations made to other "
"collectives that support the project in kind."
msgstr ""

msgid "Revenues"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"YunoHost has been always able to rely on donations to fund its activity, "
"together with occasional grants. Given the increased funding needs for this "
"new season, the team has been looking for ways to lower the financial burden "
"on the community by:"
msgstr ""

msgid "Applying for grants (with some success this year),"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Trying to partner with civil society organizations through a dedicated "
"project (with a lot of sweat but no financial success for now)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Starting to develop [a professional activity](https://yunohost.pro) which "
"aims at allowing some core contributors of the project's team to spend more "
"time on the project (some of it being paid by customers)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Here are our expected source of revenues:"
msgstr ""

msgid "**Recurring donations:** 2,500 €/month"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"**One-time donations:** ~72,000 € (~6,000 €/month) (grants included: ~42,000 "
"€ (3,500 €/month))"
msgstr ""

msgid "NLNet through NGI0 (OIDC, Packaging v3): ~34,500 €"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Code Lutin through Copie Publique (half of users self-registration): 5,000 €"
msgstr ""

msgid "Civil Society (in progress) : (~2,500 €)"
msgstr ""

msgid "Yunohost.pro (in progress): ~ 500 €"
msgstr ""

msgid "**Total budget in 2026:** ~100,000 € (~8,500 €/month)"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"To this budget must also be added the also donations in-kind, in particular "
"donations in the form of servers or bandwidth from other non-profit "
"organizations (Globenet, Gitoyen and tetaneutral) as well as independent web "
"companies (Octopuce)."
msgstr ""

